parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension and Steering System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension and steering system can cause vibration, shimmy, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: or shaking; clicking noise; pulsation or vibration of the steering wheel at speeds greater than 40 mph; loose steering; tire wear; and vibration at speeds of 50-70 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to slide or skid, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brakes sticking; odors or fumes coming from the vehicle; squeaking noise from the front end; and intermittent problem with brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheels and tires can cause vibration, tire wear, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vibration at speeds of 55-70 mph; tire wear; and vibration at speeds of 50-60 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint nut can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
The failure of the brake pedal can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes all the way to the ground
the brakes do not operate when the pedal is pressed
causing the vehicle to skid and impairing steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pads can cause grinding noises, reduced braking performance, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Grinding noise when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid lines can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.

The failure of the crankshaft pulley or bolt can cause the timing belt to break, leading to engine stalling, loss of power steering and alternator power, and potentially resulting in serious engine damage or even engine replacement.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power steering and alternator power
the crankshaft pulley bolt breaks or shears off
metal fragments are found in the engine or catalytic converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls repeatedly at low RPMs
the engine cuts off or slows down when attempting to accelerate
especially when making a complete stop.
